  <title>Circuits: Introduction</title>
	<introduction>
    <p> In this chapter you will learn about the fundamentals of circuits.</p>
	
	<p><alert>Learning Outcomes</alert></p>
  
	<p>
		After successful completion of this chapter, you will be able to:
		<ol>
			<li>Identify the conditions for current to flow through circuit components.</li>
			<li>Relate current to the flow of electric charge per unit time.</li>
			<li>Draw and label basic and advanced circuit diagrams.</li>
			<li>Treat batteries as sources of constant voltage rather than constant current.</li>
		</ol>
	</p>

